=== 数据 ===
沃森的信息来源包括[[百科全书|百科全书]]、[[字典|字典]]、词典、新闻和文学作品。沃森也使用[[数据库|数据库]]、[[分类学|分类学]]和[[本体论|本体论]]。特别是[[DBpedia|DBpedia]], [[WordNet|WordNet]],和{{tsl|en|YAGO (database)||Yago}}。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.aaai.org/Magazine/Watson/watson.php |title=存档副本 |access-date=2011-08-19 |archive-date=2020-11-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201106232453/https://www.aaai.org/Magazine/Watson/watson.php |dead-url=no }}</ref>

IBM小组为沃森提供数百万的文档，其中包括字典、百科全书和其他能建立知识库的参考材料。<ref name=nytmag/>尽管沃森在比赛中没有链接互联网，<ref>{{cite |url=http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5jOUJ_FGtwE3OlCFaOorNa3RuV_cQ?docId=CNG.1aa3e1ece3aedbb76228b6bc8e4c385e.1b1 |publisher=AFP |title=IBM's 'Watson' to take on Jeopardy! champs |date=2011-02-11 |accessdate=2011-02-19 |archive-date=2012-05-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120525040627/http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5jOUJ_FGtwE3OlCFaOorNa3RuV_cQ?docId=CNG.1aa3e1ece3aedbb76228b6bc8e4c385e.1b1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>它4TB的磁盘上仍有2亿页结构化和非结构化的信息供其使用，<ref name="contentpages"/>其中包括了维基百科的全文。<ref name="atlantic20110217" />

== 操作 ==
[[File:Watson_Answering.jpg|thumb]]

{{rquote|right|用电脑技术来解决危险边缘的问题听起来有点雷人。<!--原文：The computer's techniques for unraveling Jeopardy! clues sounded just like mine-->那机器将问题中的关键字提取出来，然后在集群簇（沃森有相当于15TB的人类知识）中彻底搜索这些关键字。<!--原文：That machine zeroes in on key words in a clue, then combs its memory（in Watson's case, a 15-terabyte data bank of human knowledge）for clusters of associations with those words.-->它会针对关键字仔细搜索能找到的信息及其上下文、分类名、答案的类型、时间、地点、性别以及其他资料。当它“认为”某个答案比较肯定时，它就会按响抢答器。对参与危险边缘的人类选手来说，这个过程是瞬间和直观的，但我深信我们的大脑也或多或少做着相同的事情<!--原文：under the hood my brain was doing more or less the same thing-->|肯·詹宁斯<ref name="threads">{{cite web |url=http://www.slate.com/id/2284721/ |title=My Puny Human Brain |author1=[[肯·詹金斯|Ken Jennings]] |work={{tsl|en|Slate (magazine)||Slate}} |publisher=Newsweek Interactive Co. LLC |date=February 16, 2011 |access-date=February 17, 2011 |archive-date=2011-02-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110218104345/http://www.slate.com/id/2284721/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>}}

危险边缘游戏中，所有选手（也包括沃森），必须等到主持人将每个线索念完，然后就绪灯亮起，第一个按下抢答器按钮的人可以获得回答问题的机会。<ref name="nytmag" /><ref>{{cite |last = Libresco |first = Leah Anthony |url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/leah-anthony-libresco/a-nontrivial-advantage-fo_b_825837.html |title = A Non-Trivial Advantage for Watson |publisher = The Huffington Post |date = 2011-02-21 |accessdate = 2011-02-21 |archive-date = 2016-03-04 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304064344/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/leah-anthony-libresco/a-nontrivial-advantage-fo_b_825837.html |dead-url = no }}</ref>沃森像接收电子文本一样得到这些线索的同时这些线索也显示给人类选手<ref name="nytmag" />。然后它会将这些线索解析为不同的关键字和句子片段，这样做是为了查找统计相关词组。<ref name=nytmag/>沃森最革新的并不是在于全新的操作算法，而是能够快速同时运行上千的证明语言分析算法来寻找正确的答案。<ref name=nytmag/><ref>{{cite |url = http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/nova/tech/will-watson-win-jeopardy.html |work = Nova ScienceNOW |title = Will Watson Win On Jeopardy!? |publisher = [[Public_Broadcasting_Service|Public Broadcasting Service]] |date = 2011-01-20 |accessdate = 2011-01-27 |archive-date = 2011-01-24 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110124210256/http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/nova/tech/will-watson-win-jeopardy.html |dead-url = no }}</ref>算法找出的相同答案越多，沃森就越肯定答案正确<ref name="nytmag" />。一旦沃森发现一个潜在的解决方法，并且这个解决方法有效，它就会核对数据库来确定答案<ref name="nytmag" />。在前20个问题中，人类选手抢答平均需要6～7秒，而沃森视听到线索来决定是否抢答。<!--原文：In a sequence of 20 mock games human participants were able to use the average six to seven seconds that Watson needed to hear the clue and decide whether to signal for responding--><ref name=nytmag/>在这段时间内，沃森还必须评价反应和判断对答案是否自信十足。<!--原文：During that time Watson also has to evaluate the response and determine if it is sufficiently confident in the result to signal--><ref name=nytmag/>在危险边缘比赛取得胜利的部分系统是用来接收“就绪”信号和检查沃森是否有足够的信心去按响抢答器的电路系统。由于电子信号传递速度比人类反应速度快许多，沃森的反应明显比人类选手要快，但是人类选手会对就绪信号灯亮起的时刻作出预测。<ref name=david>{{cite |url = http://ibmresearchnews.blogspot.com/2010/12/how-watson-sees-hears-and-speaks-to.html |title = How Watson "sees," "hears," and "speaks" to play Jeopardy! |last = David |first = David |date = 2011-01-10 |publisher = [[IBM|IBM]] |work = IBM Research blog |accessdate = 2011-02-21 |archive-date = 2017-11-05 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20171105012003/http://ibmresearchnews.blogspot.com/2010/12/how-watson-sees-hears-and-speaks-to.html |dead-url = no }}</ref>拿到抢答权后，沃森将答案按危险边缘的格式整理并用[[合成语音|电子语音]]读出<ref name="nytmag" />。沃森的语音是演员傑夫·伍德曼（{{lang|en|Jeff Woodman}}）录制的，他参与了2004年[[IBM语音合成项目|IBM语音合成项目]]<ref>{{cite |last = Avery |first = Lise |date = 2011-02-14 |title = Actor Jeff Woodman, Voice of IBM's Watson Computer |url = http://www.anythinggoesradio.com/Interviews/JeffWoodman_02_14_11.MP3 |work = Anything Goes!! |format = MP3 |accessdate = 2011-02-15 |archive-date = 2019-09-21 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190921013845/http://www.anythinggoesradio.com/Interviews/JeffWoodman_02_14_11.MP3 |dead-url = no }}（interview of Jeff Woodman）</ref>。

=== 与人类选手比较 ===
[[File:Watson_Jeopardy.jpg|thumb]]

沃森的基本工作原则是解析线索中的关键字同时寻找相关术语作为回应。这使得沃森与人类选手既有优势又有劣势<ref name="cnet" />：沃森不擅长理解线索之间的关联。所以人类选手通常比沃森更快生成思路，尤其當线索很少的的时候<ref name="nytmag" />。沃森的程序不允许其使用在未确定答案前就按响抢答器这种大众化战术。<ref name="nytmag" />一旦生成了答案沃森就会迅速反应，按下抢答器，而不会受到人类选手的[[心理战术|心理战术]]影响<ref name="nytmag" /><ref name="jenning" />。

危险边缘的工作人员使用了不同的手段来显示沃森和人类选手按下抢答器的状态<ref name="david" />，但是却一直备受争议。<!--原文：which was critical in many rounds--><ref name="jenning" />人类选手用的是一盏灯，他们需要0.1秒的时间来反应<ref>[http://biae.clemson.edu/bpc/bp/Lab/110/reaction.htm#Type%20of%20Stimulus Kosinski, R. J.（2008）. A literature review on reaction time, Clemson University.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100611222125/http://biae.clemson.edu/bpc/bp/Lab/110/reaction.htm |date=2010-06-11 }}</ref><ref name="baker174">{{cite book |title = Final Jeopardy: Man vs. Machine and the Quest to Know Everything |url = https://archive.org/details/finaljeopardyman0000bake |author = Baker, Stephen |year=2011 |publisher = {{tsl|en|Houghton Mifflin Harcourt|}} |location = Boston, New York |page = [https://archive.org/details/finaljeopardyman0000bake/page/174 174] |isbn = 0547483163}}</ref>。而沃森使用的是电子信号，能在8[[毫秒|毫秒]]内（0.008秒）激活抢答器<ref>{{cite book |title = Final Jeopardy: Man vs. Machine and the Quest to Know Everything |url = https://archive.org/details/finaljeopardyman0000bake |author = Baker, Stephen |year = 2011 |publisher={{tsl|en|Houghton Mifflin Harcourt|}} |location = Boston, New York |page = [https://archive.org/details/finaljeopardyman0000bake/page/178 178] |isbn = 0547483163}}</ref>。人类选手尝试要求补偿[[知觉延迟|知觉延迟]]造成的误差<ref name="strachan" />，但两者之间的反应时间差依旧是太大了<ref name="jenning" />。因为沃森并不需要估算就绪信号何时到达<!--原文：but the variation in the anticipation time was generally too great to fall within Watson's response time. Watson did not operate to anticipate the notification signal.--><ref name="strachan" /><ref name="baker174" />。

